   What's New:

   Check out the new safety booklets for children ages 3 - teens.  Click
   here to view the books.

   Emergency Trauma Technician Course Final Report from Howard Luke
   Academy.  The final report from the course at the Howard Luke Academy
   is filled with great information on how to handle some of the
   challenges of coordinating and delivering an ETT course in high
   schools.  The report ends with the benefits of such a course and that
   they benefits do outweigh the challenges.

   Pediatric Self-Study Modules.  The EMSC program, through a contract
   with Deborah Whitethorn, RN, EMT-III, BSN, has developed two pediatric
   self-study modules based on the Alaska Pediatric Emergency Course.  The
   modules are Pediatric Trauma and Pediatric Airway Management and
   Respiratory Distress.  Click on the titles to download the programs.
   Check out the new Emergency Medical Services for Children public
   service announcement (PSA).

